<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-309-333  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 309 333.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  February 6 1989 n299 p98(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Computer Applications quietly picks up new locale, name. (nowcalled Current Tech)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Pang, Albert.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Computer Applications acquires Taylor Systems Inc, a ComputerBayfranchisee in Milwaukee and, to avoid confusion with a Milwaukeecompany also called Computer Applications, changes its name toCurrent Tech.andP;  About 90 percent of Current Tech's 1988 sales of$80 million came from 150 major accounts.andP;  The seven-person salesforce at the newly acquired company is expected to bring in about$10 million in sales in 1989, primarily to major accounts in thesouthern Wisconsin and northern Illinois area.andP;  Current Tech's1989 plans call for expansion of its service and trainingdivisions.andP;  A staff of 39 technicians service over 42,000 CPUslocated throughout the Midwest.andP;  Training is handled by Microworx,acquired by Current Tech in Dec 1987.andP;  Kris DeWolf, Microworxdirector of sales, says the fastest-growing area for training isto medium-size companies that cannot justify in-house training.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Computer Applications Inc. (names)Current Tech (names)Taylor Systems Inc. (acquisitions and mergers)Current Tech. Microworx (marketing).andO;Topic:     AcquisitionCompaniesValue-Added ResellersGrowthSalesTraining.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>